# 0f29967445c34e01b9db5ccd1a3b6957
#: ../reception.rst:6
msgid ""
"The reception module of Lino Welfare is for managing a reception desk and"
" a waiting queue."
msgstr ""

# 83562c899aa74f70a1c089bf22dfeef5
#: ../reception.rst:9
msgid ""
"Visitors are \"checked in\" as they present themselves at the reception "
"desk, then they wait in a lounge until an agent receives them, and "
"finally they are \"checked out\" when they leave the building."
msgstr ""

# ace2538bc0104225b5c8e0a810d9020a
#: ../reception.rst:14
msgid ""
"Social agents have a possibility to see how many and which clients are "
"waiting for them. (:ddref:`reception.MyWaitingVisitors`)"
msgstr ""

# 5430f54cf3974070bb6dba29e64fa350
#: ../reception.rst:18
msgid ""
"A **reception clerk** is the user at the reception desk who welcomes "
"visitors. The reception clerk asks questions like \"What's your name?\" "
"or \"Do you have an appointment with a social agent?\". See "
":ddref:`lino.UserProfiles`."
msgstr ""

# d4f7f40b000747faacc2d80493630248
#: ../reception.rst:27
msgid ""
"Vocabulary note: Visitors are instances of the :ddref:`cal.Guest` model "
"when they are being managed by the reception module, i.e. when they have "
"been at least checked in."
msgstr ""

# f174e5de64f3484192d1e31bd336fe24
#: ../reception.rst:32
msgid ""
"Visitors must be registered as a :ddref:`pcsw.Client`. Technically a "
":ddref:`contacts.Partner` account would be enough, but other \"visitors\""
" like suppliers or board members aren't managed by the reception module "
"of Lino Welfare."
msgstr ""

# 957da6c5a5a04e0db02e13cef16b8af3
#: ../reception.rst:37
msgid ""
"Lino notifies the user to read the client's eID card if this is "
"necessary, e.g. because \"eID card has not yet been read!\" or \"Old eID "
"card validity has expired!\""
msgstr ""

# 804cc3fdb04e4ed6b0a44492c70b6d95
#: ../reception.rst:41
msgid ""
"Most visitors come at the open consultation hours. and don't have an "
"appointment with some user. We call this a \"visit\" or \"prompt event\"."
" In that case the reception clerk clicks \"Create Visit\", confirms the "
"selected agent and enters a \"reason\" (a short one-line text). This will"
" automatically create two records: an :ddref:`cal.Event` and a "
":ddref:`cal.Guest`."
msgstr ""

# 57b9e5306fad49e8b09df4000c9c40d3
#: ../reception.rst:51
msgid ""
"A **visit** or **prompt event** is an unplanned :ddref:`cal.Event`. An "
"**appointment** is a planned (scheduled) :ddref:`cal.Event`."
msgstr ""

